channel.title: Compiler
channel.description:
Hey people. I started making my server earlier. Still [b]alot[/b] of work to do. Basically so far I've changed everything from 'PhoneScape' to the name of my server and changed the starter outfit. With help from zomgs, thanks alot mate.
Anyway, when I tried to compile after changing the outfit it said I haden't installed JDK 6/5.0. (Which I had)
Soooo I'm re-installing it right now. I'm not using Taharok's compiler, I'm using another but trust me it's good. It says the same thing as Taharok's though, go to Mod Taharok's topic etc.
I'm at the point of installation where it says this :
[code]Custom Setup Select the features you wan't installed.[/code]
These are the options.
[code]Development Tools Demos and Samples Source code Public JRE[/code]
If anyone is able to help I'd be very appreciative. (No you won't get Admin on my server :P) If anymore detail is needed just ask I'll be glad to add.[br][size=1]Posted on: April 07, 2007, 04:33:52 PM[/size][hr]Can anyone help atall? I know it's a touchy subject but some of you must be able to speak from experience.

item.title: Compiler
item.dc:creator: @damon damon
item.description:
@damon wrote:

go to

c:/program files/java

and look at the folder called jdk and copy the entire folder name and add it to

c:/program files/java/replace this txt with the copied name/bin/javac" *.java

then right click on the compiler and go edit

@echo off
“javac” *.java <------ delete that line and add
pause

@echo off
c:/program files/java/replace this txt with the copied name/bin/javac" *.java
pause

that should be ur compiler
